#| msgid "F-Droid verifies reproducible builds using the APK signature, which requires [copying](https://github.com/obfusk/apksigcopier) the signature from a signed APK to an unsigned one and then checking if the latter verifies.  The old v1 (JAR) signatures only cover the *contents* of the APK (ZIP metadata and ordering are irrelevant), but v2/v3 signatures cover *all other bytes in the APK*.  Thus, the APKs must be completely identical *before* and *after* signing (apart from the signature) in order to verify correctly."
msgid "F-Droid verifies reproducible builds using the [APK signature](https://source.android.com/docs/security/features/apksigning)  (a form of [embedded signature](https://reproducible-builds.org/docs/embedded-signatures/)), which requires [copying](https://github.com/obfusk/apksigcopier) the signature from a signed APK to an unsigned one and then checking if the latter verifies.  The old v1 (JAR) signatures only cover the *contents* of the APK (e.g. ZIP metadata and ordering are irrelevant), but v2/v3 signatures cover *all other bytes in the APK*.  Thus, the APKs must be completely identical *before* and *after* signing (apart from the signature) in order to verify correctly."
msgstr "O F-Droid verifica compilações reproduzíveis pela assinatura APK, que requer [copiar](https://github.com/obfusk/apksigcopier) a assinatura de um APK assinado a um APK não assinado e depois verificar se o último verifica.  As assinaturas antigas v1 (JAR) cobrem apenas o *conteúdo* do APK (metadados ZIP e ordenação são irrelevantes), mas as assinaturas v2/v3 cobrem *todos os outros bytes no APK*.  Assim, os APKs devem ser completamente idênticos *antes* e *depois* da assinatura (além da assinatura) para se poder verificar corretamente."

